              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">March 19, 2026</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 2581</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Soria<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 20, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add Section 50158 to the Health and Safety Code, relating to housing. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 2581, as amended, Soria.
                          Housing: affordable housing tenants:<font color="#B30000"><strike> homeownership.</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> home ownership.</i></font></span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law prescribes the general responsibilities and roles of the Department of Housing and Community Development and the California Housing Finance Agency in carrying out state housing policies and programs. Existing law establishes various programs to promote development of affordable housing for tenants and homeowners, including the Multifamily Housing Program, low-income housing tax credits, and the Joe Serna, Jr. Farmworker Housing Grant Program.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would, by January 1, 2028, require the department and the agency to develop and implement<font color="#B30000"><strike> strategies</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> strategies, as specified,</i></font> to promote the movement of tenants of deed-restricted affordable
			 housing into<font color="#B30000"><strike> homeownership</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> home ownership</i></font> through existing<font color="#B30000"><strike> homeownership</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> home ownership</i></font> programs implemented by the department or the agency.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.2785054908604895"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Section 50158 is added to the Health and Safety Code, to read:</div><div><div id="id_9D572468-47AA-46CC-ABCA-D2392EB12730"><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">50158.</h6> <font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(a) </i></font>By January 1, 2028, the Department of Housing and Community Development and the California Housing Finance Agency shall develop and implement strategies to promote the movement of tenants of deed-restricted affordable housing into<font color="#B30000"><strike> homeownership</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i> home ownership</i></font> through existing<font color="#B30000"><strike> homeownership</strike></font><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>
						home ownership</i></font> programs implemented by the department or the agency.</div><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) The strategies developed and implemented pursuant to subdivision (a) shall include, but not be limited to, advertising of existing home ownership programs to tenants of deed-restricted affordable housing.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(c) For the purposes of this section, “existing home ownership programs” shall include, but not be limited to, any of the following:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(1) The Joe Serna, Jr. Farmworker Housing Grant Program established pursuant to Chapter 3.2 (commencing with Section 50515.2) of Part 2.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) The CalHome Program established pursuant to Chapter 6 (commencing with Section
						50650) of Part 2.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(3) The home purchase assistance program established pursuant to Chapter 6.8 (commencing with Section 51341) of Part 3.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(4) The California Dream for All Program established pursuant to Chapter 12 (commencing with Section 51520) of Part 3.</div></i></font></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
